Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithms for solving hard combinatorial problems, specifically SAT and #SAT, by exploiting hidden structure in the form of decomposability and strong backdoor sets. This falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of treewidth and cycle cutsets also suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the study of counting satisfying assignments relates to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
